#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-membership-agreement.md:1
msgid "Membership Agreement for the Code of Conduct (CoC) Committee"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-membership-agreement.md:3
msgid ""
"This document describes the responsibilities that the members of the Code"
" of Conduct committee (CoCc) must agree to meet in order to fulfill the "
"requirements of their roles on the committee."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-membership-agreement.md:5
msgid ""
"The committee is what turns a code of conduct from a written document "
"into meaningful action.<br />Valerie Aurora, FrameShift Consulting"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-membership-agreement.md:8
msgid "Core Membership Agreement:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-membership-agreement.md:10
msgid ""
"The main purpose of the CoCc is to: establish, maintain and uphold the "
"Code of Conduct; educate members of the community of policies and "
"behaviors that can help create a more inclusive and welcoming "
"environment; and protect all members from harm in community spaces."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-membership-agreement.md:12
msgid "In order to uphold the CoC, the CoCc members will:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-membership-agreement.md:14
msgid ""
"support the objectives and mission of The Carpentries by abiding by its "
"CoC and other policies and procedures."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-membership-agreement.md:15
msgid ""
"learn about the Code of Conduct and reporting guidelines, and as CoC "
"advocates, bring awareness of it into any Community spaces that they are "
"part of."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-membership-agreement.md:16
msgid ""
"understand and be comfortable to act on CoC related reports as per the "
"enforcement guidelines put in place for the relevant community spaces."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-membership-agreement.md:17
msgid ""
"actively help develop and maintain existing and new documents to "
"facilitate the work of the CoCc."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-membership-agreement.md:18
msgid ""
"avoid conflicts of interest [1] when processing CoC related reports. "
"Failure to declare a conflict of interest may be considered a breach of "
"the CoC."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-membership-agreement.md:19
msgid ""
"maintain the confidentiality of any reported incidents, the identity of "
"persons involved and discussions that take place within the committee."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-membership-agreement.md:20
msgid ""
"not make any comments about any matters that they have been informed of "
"as part of their duties as a CoCc member unless authorized to do so."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-membership-agreement.md:21
msgid ""
"hold themselves accountable for their responsibilities as trustees and "
"understand that they are expected to follow through on their commitments."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-membership-agreement.md:22
msgid ""
"respect and promote diversity, equity, and inclusion in the community and"
" act in the best interests of the Carpentries community impartially, "
"putting aside any individual affiliations such as organizations or other "
"Carpentries committees, and personal biases."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-membership-agreement.md:25
msgid "Further Roles and Responsibilities:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-membership-agreement.md:27
msgid ""
"In addition to the core membership agreement, CoCc members will be "
"required to:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-membership-agreement.md:29
msgid ""
"support the committee chair and the designated Core Team liaison in "
"collective decision making. In order to do so, they will prepare fully "
"for meetings, which will include reading reports and related documents "
"carefully, querying anything they do not understand, thinking through "
"issues before meetings and completing any tasks assigned to them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-membership-agreement.md:30
#, python-format
msgid ""
"attend in the order of 75% of all CoCc Business meetings [2]. In these "
"meetings, CoCc members will actively engage in discussion, voting and "
"contributing in a constructive way, listening carefully, challenging "
"sensitively and avoiding conflict."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-membership-agreement.md:31
msgid ""
"promptly respond to emails, or, if they realize they will be out of touch"
" for a while, inform the committee chair."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-membership-agreement.md:32
msgid ""
"participate in any training that is organized to support the work of the "
"committee, and to responsibly use any technical solutions that the CoCc "
"is asked to use in order to maintain the security and privacy of personal"
" information conveyed to the committee."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-membership-agreement.md:35
msgid "[1] Note on Conflicts of Interest:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-membership-agreement.md:37
msgid ""
"A conflict of interest is a situation where a member of the CoCc could be"
" perceived to not act in the interest of the Carpentries and the members "
"of the community. Such situations can, for instance, occur when the "
"members have close ties with one of the parties in a CoC incident (e.g. "
"family relationships, close friendships, business ties, or even personal "
"considerations). Such conflicts of interest may make it difficult to "
"fulfill their duties impartially."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-membership-agreement.md:40
msgid ""
"If any member of the committee happens to face a conflict of interest "
"while handling a case, they are  expected to:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-membership-agreement.md:41
msgid ""
"inform the chair of the CoCc and/or the full committee of the conflict of"
" interest,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-membership-agreement.md:42
msgid ""
"not be involved in the case, and if required, temporarily leave their "
"position as a CoCc member to avoid any bias."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-membership-agreement.md:45
msgid "[2] Note on the CoCc Meetings:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-membership-agreement.md:47
msgid "The committee conducts two types of meetings:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-membership-agreement.md:49
msgid ""
"Business meetings: these are meetings where we discuss the status of "
"current documents, issues brought to us by the community and other CoC "
"related matters."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-membership-agreement.md:50
msgid ""
"Incident report related meetings: in these meetings those that have "
"volunteered to decide the course of action for a reported incident meet "
"and discuss the situation. To decide on an issue, a minimum of 3 members "
"must participate, thus not all members need to participate in every case."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-membership-agreement.md:53
msgid "Onboarding of new committee members:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-membership-agreement.md:55
msgid ""
"New committee members will be included in committee discussions only "
"after they have fulfilled the onboarding requirements specified by the "
"CoCc and The Carpentries Executive Council."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-membership-agreement.md:58
msgid "Leaving the Committee:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-membership-agreement.md:60
msgid ""
"If a CoCc member wishes to leave the committee at any time, they will "
"inform the Committee chair in advance (giving enough notice to hand-over "
"their responsibility) in writing, stating their reasons for leaving."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/policies/coc-membership-agreement.md:61
msgid ""
"Breach of any part of the CoC by any CoCc member may result in a fair "
"procedure being put in motion that may result in them being asked to "
"resign from the CoCc. Should this happen they will be given the "
"opportunity to be heard. In the event they are asked to resign from the "
"committee, they will accept the majority decision of the committee in "
"this matter and resign at the earliest opportunity."
msgstr ""

